Input Handling: Handle user input or input from external sources. This could include reading from files, receiving input from the user via the command line or a GUI, etc.
Processing Logic: Write the logic that processes the input data. This could involve calculations, data manipulation, decision-making, etc.
Output Handling: Handle the output of your program. This could involve displaying results to the user, writing data to files, sending data over a network, etc.
Error Handling: Include mechanisms to handle errors and exceptions gracefully. This could include try-catch blocks, error messages, logging, etc.
Cleanup and Finalization: Perform any necessary cleanup tasks before the program exits. This could include closing files, releasing resources, etc.
